New Records: Travis Head scored a career-best 154 not out.
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten 154 led Australia to a seven-wicket victory.
England were restricted to 315 all out by a spin-heavy Australian bowling attack.
Adam Zampa, playing his 100th ODI, took three wickets for 22 runs in his last seven overs.
Marnus Labuschagne took a career-best three for 39 from six overs.
Ben Duckett scored 95 and Will Jacks scored 62 for England.
Australia chased down the target with six overs to spare.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia were missing key players like Pat Cummins, Josh Hazlewood, Mitchell Starc, and Glenn Maxwell due to rest and illness.
Post-Match Reflections: Marcus Trescothick, England’s interim white-ball head coach, acknowledged the team's good efforts but noted the pitch improvement and the toss as significant factors.
Harry Brook, the stand-in England captain, faced a challenging start to his captaincy.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Trent Bridge, where England previously set two record one-day international totals.
The pitch conditions improved as the match progressed, favoring the team batting second.
